cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.DL, cs.ET, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the use of a virtual community and collaboration protocol for pedagogical purposes, which falls under the category of computer-supported collaborative learning (cs.CY) and computer-supported education (cs.CE). The use of a web-based collaboration environment also relates to digital libraries (cs.DL) and educational technology (cs.ET). Finally, the paper discusses the successful outcome of an experiment involving graduate-level mathematics students, which could also be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) in the context of educational technology.
